'''鏡頭恐懼'''（{{lang-en|Ipovlopsychophobia}}）是指当[[鏡頭|鏡頭]]在眼前晃動時會感到[[恐懼|恐懼]]及不舒服，認為鏡頭正在捕捉自己靈魂的一部分，出於本能地會想閃躲以免被捕捉。<ref name=drgeorge>{{cite web|last=George |first=Dr |url=http://counsellingresource.com/ask-the-psychologist/2009/06/17/what-do-you-call-a-fear-of-being-photographed/ |title=What Do You Call a Fear of Being Photographed? |publisher=Counsellingresource.com |date= |accessdate=2013-06-03}}</ref>

==语源==
“Ipovlopsychophobia”一词源自[[希腊语|希腊语]]，是ὑποβλώψ（ypovló̱ps，窥视者<ref>[http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3Du(poblw%2Fy&highlight=stolen ὑποβλώψ], Henry George Liddell, Robert Scott, ''A Greek-English Lexicon'', on Perseus</ref>）、ψυχή（psychí̱，灵魂<ref>[http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3Dyuxh%2F&highlight=soul ψυχή], Henry George Liddell, Robert Scott, ''A Greek-English Lexicon'', on Perseus</ref>）和φόβος（phobos，恐惧<ref>[http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3Dfo%2Fbos φόβος], Henry George Liddell, Robert Scott, ''A Greek-English Lexicon'', on Perseus</ref>）的合成词，用来表示一个人抗拒被摄入影像，害怕自己的样子出现在不受自己控制的地方。有少部分的宗教教义认为，人的[[灵魂|灵魂]]或[[精神|精气]]会被摄影者摄入影像或影像器材中。<ref name=drgeorge />

